description._content: TITLE West Street in Keene New Hampshire CREATOR French, J.A., Keene NH SUBJECT Streets - NH - Keene Buildings - NH - Keene DESCRIPTION Stereograph of a snow scene on West Street in Keene New Hampshire. First called Piety Lane and then Pleasant Street, it was also known at one time as Mill Street, probably due to the extensive area covered by Faulkner & Colony Mfg. Co. Laid out about 1740, this early route left Main Street and then turned northwesterly across house lots now on the south side of West Street and entered the present West at the corner of School Street. It passed "Maccany Plain", on which West Keene is built, in its course over West Hill to Chesterfield.
